verbose_text: Plasma levels of AOPPs (P < 0.001), BALP (P < 0.001) and TRACP 5b (P < 0.001) were statistically significantly increased in the postmenopausal osteoporotic women compared with controls, but there was no statistically significant difference in MDA (P = 0.124) between the 2 groups.
evidence: levels of AOPPs (P<0.001), BALP (P<0.001) and TRACP 5b
